Subject: [PATCH] Isabelle: feed isabellized axioms to the proof method; escript-safe TPTP.thy

Against atp_client 0.6.0. Apply with `patch -p1` from the repo root.
Fix 1 depends on the companion isabelle_elixir patch (adds TPTP.source_text/0).

--- Fix 1: ensure_tptp_theory/1 -- escript-safe TPTP.thy placement

  File.cp(TPTP.source_path(), dest) reads through priv/, which does not resolve
  when the caller is escript-packaged (as AtpMcp is): the escript is a zip file,
  so the read fails :enotdir and prove_tptp/3 always returns
  {:error, {:tptp_thy_copy_failed, :enotdir}}. Write the embedded text instead.

--- Fix 2: inject_proof_method/2 -- `using <axioms>` (the substantive one)

  isabellize_theory/1 renders TPTP axioms as `axiomatization where a1: "..."`.
  Isabelle does NOT hand those to a tactic automatically, and inject_proof_method/2
  emitted only the bare method:

      lemma g: "(mortal @ socrates)"
        by auto

  so the goal was attempted against HOL alone and every problem that depends on
  its own axioms came back gave_up. The theory itself loads fine (19/20 steps
  OK); Isabelle reports only:

      Failed to apply initial proof method: goal (1 subgoal): 1. mortal @ socrates

  Confirmed by hand on a THF syllogism (human/mortal/socrates):
      "by auto"              -> {:ok, :gave_up}
      "using a1 a2 by auto"  -> {:ok, :theorem}
      "using a1 a2 by metis" -> {:ok, :theorem}

  This is severe and silent: gave_up is also what an honest failure looks like,
  so the backend appeared to work while never proving anything non-trivial.
  AtpMcp compounds it -- opts_from(args, "isabelle") allows only
  [:use_theories_timeout_ms, :raw], so :proof_method cannot be passed over MCP
  and callers cannot work around it.

  Now collects the axiomatization names and prefixes the method with
  `using <names> `. With no axioms the output is byte-identical to today.

  REVIEW NOTE: this changes generated theories for every caller, including
  :proof_method "sledgehammer nitpick oops" (becomes `using a1 a2 sledgehammer
  ...`, which chains the facts -- intended, but your call). An alternative is
  emitting the axioms as [simp]; `using` was chosen as the least surprising and
  method-agnostic option.

VERIFIED (both fixes, atp_mcp 0.5.1 escript built against patched deps, driven
over stdio JSON-RPC, no TPTP.thy pre-placed):
    query_backend isabelle, provable THF   -> Theorem   (was :enotdir, then GaveUp)
    query_backend isabelle, unprovable THF -> GaveUp    (no false positives)
  No regressions: verify_backend isabelle OK; prove_isabelle Theorem / GaveUp;
  query_backend local_exec Theorem; lint_problem OK.

STILL OPEN (not addressed here)
  * FOF input isabellizes to an empty body ("\n") -> no lemmas ->
    aggregate_lemma_results([]) -> {:ok, :gave_up}. Unsupported input is thus
    indistinguishable from a failed proof; this path is THF-only. Worth an
    explicit {:error, {:unsupported_dialect, :fof}} instead.
  * :raw is accepted but ignored on the prove_tptp path -- query/2 collapses to
    a status, so raw output never reaches the caller.

--- a/lib/atp_client/isabelle.ex
+++ b/lib/atp_client/isabelle.ex
@@ -656,24 +656,43 @@
   end
 
   defp inject_proof_method(isabellized, proof_method) do
+    using = using_clause(axiom_names(isabellized))
+
     isabellized
     |> String.split(~r/\n\n+/)
     |> Enum.map_join("\n\n", fn item ->
       if String.starts_with?(String.trim_leading(item), "lemma ") do
-        String.trim_trailing(item) <> "\n  " <> proof_method
+        String.trim_trailing(item) <> "\n  " <> using <> proof_method
       else
         item
       end
     end)
   end
 
+  # The isabellizer renders TPTP axioms as `axiomatization where <name>: …`.
+  # Isabelle does not hand those to a tactic on its own, so without an explicit
+  # `using` the goal is attempted against HOL alone and any problem that
+  # actually depends on its axioms comes back `gave_up` — silently, since that
+  # is also what an honest failure looks like.
+  defp axiom_names(isabellized) do
+    ~r/^\s*axiomatization\s+where\s+([A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_']*)\s*:/m
+    |> Regex.scan(isabellized)
+    |> Enum.map(fn [_, name] -> name end)
+  end
+
+  defp using_clause([]), do: ""
+  defp using_clause(names), do: "using " <> Enum.join(names, " ") <> " "
+
   defp ensure_tptp_theory(local_dir) do
     dest = Path.join(local_dir, "TPTP.thy")
 
     if File.exists?(dest) do
       :ok
     else
-      case File.cp(TPTP.source_path(), dest) do
+      # Write the embedded copy rather than File.cp/2 from TPTP.source_path/0:
+      # that path lives under priv/ and does not resolve when the caller is an
+      # escript (as AtpMcp is), which fails the copy with :enotdir.
+      case File.write(dest, TPTP.source_text()) do
         :ok -> :ok
         {:error, reason} -> {:error, {:tptp_thy_copy_failed, reason}}
       end
